WEBVTT

00:00:01.495 --> 00:00:08.609 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
The 1981 version of the film, complete
with fragments removed by the censors.

00:00:21.025 --> 00:00:23.701 line:85% position:50% size:80%
TOR Film Studio

00:00:34.375 --> 00:00:36.518 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Noooo!!!

00:00:45.875 --> 00:00:47.161 line:85% position:50% size:80%
in

00:00:47.625 --> 00:00:51.762 line:85% position:50% size:80%
BLIND CHANCE

00:00:52.542 --> 00:00:55.360 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Written and Directed by

00:01:20.875 --> 00:01:22.251 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Go on, write it down.

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:39.593 line:85% position:50% size:80%
17 - 9 = 8

00:01:41.125 --> 00:01:44.754 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Good. Your mother wrote
her 8s the same way.

00:01:52.542 --> 00:01:53.692 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Daniel!

00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:05.123 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I'm not going as far as I thought.
Only to Denmark.

00:02:05.542 --> 00:02:07.161 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I'll write to you.

00:02:11.877 --> 00:02:14.937 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
It's not an internal matter
for the school any more.

00:02:15.375 --> 00:02:17.311 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Let's go through the names.

00:02:17.792 --> 00:02:19.915 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Łubin.
- Fairly obvious.

00:02:20.292 --> 00:02:21.496 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Who was he?

00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:25.318 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
A Prime Minister. Caught making out
with a custodian last year.

00:02:25.403 --> 00:02:27.637 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
That's even worse.
We can transfer him.

00:02:27.741 --> 00:02:30.917 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Kamiński has three failing grades,
also obvious.

00:02:31.002 --> 00:02:32.831 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- How about Długosz?
- Who was he?

00:02:32.917 --> 00:02:34.956 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Minister of Health.
- He's a half-orphan.

00:02:35.042 --> 00:02:38.165 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Great grades, exemplary
behavior.

00:02:39.337 --> 00:02:41.860 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Has leadership skills
but everybody likes him.

00:02:57.082 --> 00:02:58.383 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Fuck her!

00:03:00.185 --> 00:03:01.411 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Fuck her!

00:03:46.957 --> 00:03:48.239 line:85% position:50% size:80%
What's wrong?

00:03:49.707 --> 00:03:51.646 line:85% position:50% size:80%
She used to be my teacher.

00:03:52.917 --> 00:03:54.080 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I hated her.

00:03:57.167 --> 00:03:59.697 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You've never noticed
me before, have you?

00:04:03.750 --> 00:04:09.283 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You'd get skates or a bike but
I never liked your good grades.

00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:12.068 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You knew that, didn't you?

00:04:14.667 --> 00:04:17.156 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You know what made
me really happy?

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.305 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You beating up a teacher
when you were thirteen.

00:04:21.958 --> 00:04:24.355 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Nothing but straight Cs
after that.

00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:29.836 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I never liked overachievers.
Especially in life.

00:04:30.240 --> 00:04:32.795 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And that included your school.

00:04:33.072 --> 00:04:34.490 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You're still here?

00:04:38.458 --> 00:04:40.915 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Kasia, this is my son.

00:04:45.583 --> 00:04:46.728 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Witek.

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:16.083 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- The room is only ours for an hour.
- I have to make a call.

00:05:19.875 --> 00:05:22.324 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You always call and
never say a thing.

00:05:26.416 --> 00:05:29.786 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Witek? Is that you?
- Yes.

00:05:31.831 --> 00:05:32.827 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Yes, Dad.

00:05:32.913 --> 00:05:35.706 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
They're taking me
to the hospital. Kasia's here.

00:05:35.791 --> 00:05:38.815 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
In case I don't see you...
You don't have to do anything.

00:05:38.901 --> 00:05:40.802 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Do what?
- Nothing at all.

00:05:40.916 --> 00:05:42.084 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Dad!

00:05:46.500 --> 00:05:47.415 line:85% position:50% size:80%
My father.

00:05:55.041 --> 00:05:56.654 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Pissing or puking?

00:06:02.625 --> 00:06:04.153 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You're lucky.

00:06:17.958 --> 00:06:21.113 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- You lost your vocation?
- That's right.

00:06:22.625 --> 00:06:23.802 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And?

00:06:26.583 --> 00:06:29.812 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
My late father
wanted me to be a doctor.

00:06:30.038 --> 00:06:33.190 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But on his deathbed he told me
he didn't want it anymore.

00:06:33.276 --> 00:06:35.459 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I need some time to think.

00:06:35.625 --> 00:06:40.889 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Of course. Though it's a pity.
- You've got milk whiskers, sir.

00:06:42.952 --> 00:06:48.245 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
<i>The train to Warsaw East Station
</i><i>will depart from Platform 2.</i>

00:06:58.333 --> 00:06:59.331 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Are you blind?

00:06:59.416 --> 00:07:02.158 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- You'll break your neck!
- Sorry.

00:07:02.791 --> 00:07:04.697 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He spilled all my change...

00:07:20.865 --> 00:07:22.180 line:85% position:50% size:80%
A beer, please.

00:07:32.958 --> 00:07:35.576 line:85% position:50% size:80%
A student ticket to Warsaw.

00:07:39.213 --> 00:07:40.331 line:85% position:50% size:80%
One to Łomża.

00:08:29.458 --> 00:08:31.074 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You were lucky.

00:08:31.894 --> 00:08:34.687 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- You could've missed it.
- Yeah. I almost have.

00:08:43.417 --> 00:08:45.106 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Feet off the seat!

00:08:45.207 --> 00:08:48.268 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- May I go to the restroom?
- Go.

00:08:52.625 --> 00:08:54.677 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Don't get lost on the way.

00:09:22.707 --> 00:09:25.976 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Scram. It's your chance.

00:09:27.332 --> 00:09:29.126 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I'll give you my sneakers.

00:09:55.875 --> 00:09:57.399 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He wouldn't run?

00:09:59.582 --> 00:10:00.711 line:85% position:50% size:80%
No.

00:10:03.471 --> 00:10:07.916 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Sometimes people don't run.
Because they don't want to.

00:10:10.542 --> 00:10:14.999 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Repeated beatings
on the shinbone

00:10:15.582 --> 00:10:18.408 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
leave you with
a permanent limp.

00:10:44.875 --> 00:10:48.754 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
It used to taste better...
I pleaded guilty at the trial.

00:10:49.875 --> 00:10:56.789 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But it took me time to realize
that standing for my ideals

00:10:56.875 --> 00:11:04.677 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
meant admitting to
things I've never done or thought.

00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:17.429 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
And Krystyna was waiting...
for freedom.

00:11:19.370 --> 00:11:21.873 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Did I tell you what she was like?
- You did.

00:11:21.957 --> 00:11:24.224 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Everything about her was pale.

00:11:24.375 --> 00:11:26.866 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Somewhat peculiar for a woman

00:11:27.582 --> 00:11:35.913 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
who had some fair fuzz above her
upper lip and near her ears.

00:11:36.625 --> 00:11:38.450 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And large, ugly hands.

00:11:40.332 --> 00:11:45.860 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Maybe that was why I touched her.
Because of her imperfections.

00:11:47.299 --> 00:11:54.138 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
She couldn't take her ring
off those fat fingers...

00:11:57.000 --> 00:12:02.211 line:85% position:50% size:80%
When Adam was arrested in 1949.

00:12:06.125 --> 00:12:10.623 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Back then, in 1949,
it meant that he was a spy.

00:12:10.707 --> 00:12:12.998 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He wasn't, but who cared?

00:12:13.082 --> 00:12:15.980 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
It took me a year
to convince her.

00:12:17.375 --> 00:12:21.586 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And so, I've moved in with her.

00:12:26.792 --> 00:12:30.592 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- We called already?
- Yes. No answer.

00:12:32.542 --> 00:12:33.886 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And now?

00:12:34.957 --> 00:12:38.835 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I still believe, but do they?

00:12:40.957 --> 00:12:44.498 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
When they arrested me
and I pleaded guilty

00:12:44.582 --> 00:12:50.701 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
she started to doubt whether
she was married to a spy.

00:12:51.832 --> 00:12:54.140 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Even though
I convinced her she was.

00:12:54.225 --> 00:12:56.291 line:85% position:50% size:80%
That's why she couldn't believe

00:12:56.375 --> 00:13:00.623 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
that I also was against
the Party and Communism.

00:13:00.707 --> 00:13:06.595 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
She stopped believing the Party.
She only believed herself.

00:13:07.582 --> 00:13:09.740 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We were in the same prison.

00:13:11.125 --> 00:13:13.405 line:85% position:50% size:80%
She would visit both of us.

00:13:16.667 --> 00:13:18.428 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We walked past one another...

00:13:21.042 --> 00:13:26.344 line:85% position:50% size:80%
She was even whiter and paler then

00:13:29.207 --> 00:13:33.166 line:85% position:50% size:80%
and had that fuzz above her lip.

00:13:38.566 --> 00:13:43.182 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Dial. 45-21-95.

00:13:56.207 --> 00:13:58.177 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Hello?
- Ask for Krystyna.

00:13:58.292 --> 00:14:01.067 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
It's a public phone,
hence the poor connection.

00:14:01.153 --> 00:14:03.413 line:85% position:50% size:80%
May I talk to Krystyna, please?

00:14:05.082 --> 00:14:08.904 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Say you're from the Institute.

00:14:09.167 --> 00:14:11.248 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I'm from the Institute.

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:19.652 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Hello, it's me. Krystyna?

00:14:20.750 --> 00:14:23.475 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I came back a few hours ago.

00:14:24.667 --> 00:14:26.451 line:85% position:50% size:80%
But you weren't there...

00:14:30.417 --> 00:14:33.201 line:85% position:50% size:80%
<i>No trouble sleeping lately?</i>

00:14:38.346 --> 00:14:39.456 line:85% position:50% size:80%
<i>What?</i>

00:14:42.875 --> 00:14:43.975 line:85% position:50% size:80%
<i>Hania?</i>

00:14:47.682 --> 00:14:49.110 line:85% position:50% size:80%
<i>You're a grandmother?</i>

00:15:39.125 --> 00:15:43.479 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I was away for a few days
and I'm leaving again soon

00:15:43.565 --> 00:15:46.418 line:85% position:50% size:80%
so I haven't done any shopping.

00:15:59.082 --> 00:16:02.028 line:85% position:50% size:80%
No, I can't eat at this hour.

00:16:06.250 --> 00:16:09.400 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Well?
- Have I shown you her picture?

00:16:11.082 --> 00:16:13.081 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I haven't and I won't.

00:16:13.167 --> 00:16:15.480 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I hope you meet her some day.

00:16:15.832 --> 00:16:19.451 line:85% position:50% size:80%
This picture is thirty years old,

00:16:20.457 --> 00:16:27.783 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
and I don't want you to have
too specific ideas about those times.

00:16:29.332 --> 00:16:31.232 line:85% position:50% size:80%
When did you get out?

00:16:32.207 --> 00:16:36.841 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Not soon enough. They started
releasing spies in 1954.

00:16:37.688 --> 00:16:43.932 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Us, the "dissenters", were
kept longer.

00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:59.831 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
By the time I got out,
they'd been together for over a year.

00:17:00.707 --> 00:17:02.020 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And you?

00:17:02.750 --> 00:17:11.433 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I was given this apartment, and
moved in... For good, I suppose.

00:17:13.041 --> 00:17:15.750 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
And here is where
you believe in all that?

00:17:16.375 --> 00:17:19.556 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Here... and anywhere else.

00:17:20.375 --> 00:17:26.631 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Maybe being here
makes it easier to believe.

00:17:28.333 --> 00:17:35.512 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I'm sort of... more equal here.

00:17:37.375 --> 00:17:44.046 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Mind you, after prison I never
wanted to be less equal.

00:17:45.166 --> 00:17:47.538 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Not that I didn't get
tempting offers.

00:17:47.625 --> 00:17:55.386 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Some of my fellow inmates
had a lot to offer.

00:17:55.625 --> 00:17:58.481 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But you can see
what's happening to all that.

00:18:00.583 --> 00:18:02.196 line:85% position:50% size:80%
It's very simple.

00:18:02.458 --> 00:18:11.451 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
If we didn't manage to do it,
maybe this generation will.

00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:16.451 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You, for instance.

00:18:19.791 --> 00:18:22.297 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Want a blanket?
- Yes, please.

00:18:28.291 --> 00:18:33.128 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Go to bed. I'll stay up
a little longer.

00:18:34.208 --> 00:18:39.050 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
There is another
blanket on the bed.

00:18:39.458 --> 00:18:42.227 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I have several blankets...

00:18:59.291 --> 00:19:05.539 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
My father died ten days ago.
I didn't make it to his bedside.

00:19:05.625 --> 00:19:12.205 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But I got his final message:
there's nothing I have to do.

00:19:31.125 --> 00:19:32.342 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Witek! Come here.

00:19:37.083 --> 00:19:40.167 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- This is Mr. Długosz.
- What's he doing?

00:19:40.604 --> 00:19:44.192 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Fourth year of medical school,
currently on Dean's leave.

00:19:44.665 --> 00:19:46.746 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Second thoughts about
becoming a doctor?

00:19:46.830 --> 00:19:48.063 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Yes.

00:19:48.416 --> 00:19:51.284 line:85% position:50% size:80%
So, now we know everything.

00:19:52.166 --> 00:19:54.050 line:85% position:50% size:80%
See if we can get started.

00:19:59.583 --> 00:20:01.915 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Have you read this?
- Yes.

00:20:02.173 --> 00:20:03.481 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Any comments?

00:20:03.958 --> 00:20:07.309 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I agree with what you write.

00:20:07.500 --> 00:20:08.611 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You write well.

00:20:10.250 --> 00:20:12.758 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
It's pretty much all
that you do well.

00:20:14.125 --> 00:20:15.887 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We're ready for you.

00:20:20.458 --> 00:20:22.800 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- You want to listen?
- I'd love to.

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:32.867 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Werner is leaving in three weeks.
- And for a long time.

00:20:33.625 --> 00:20:37.810 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Should you need anything,
let me know.

00:20:46.666 --> 00:20:51.351 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I know exactly what I want to say.

00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:53.758 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I don't need notes.

00:20:54.375 --> 00:20:59.663 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I wish to present my current views

00:20:59.958 --> 00:21:08.349 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
on the concept
I've adhered to for forty years.

00:21:09.708 --> 00:21:15.355 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Each generation desires
some kind of light;

00:21:16.458 --> 00:21:19.253 line:85% position:50% size:80%
needs assurance and faith

00:21:20.083 --> 00:21:25.143 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
that the world can be just
and better organized.

00:21:27.083 --> 00:21:33.740 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
This desire, older than Marx
and younger than Marx,

00:21:34.333 --> 00:21:36.571 line:85% position:50% size:80%
is like a drug.

00:21:38.250 --> 00:21:40.748 line:85% position:50% size:80%
At the beginning, it brings joy

00:21:40.833 --> 00:21:44.689 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
because the light
seems within reach.

00:21:45.541 --> 00:21:48.416 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Towards the end,
it brings bitterness

00:21:49.750 --> 00:21:52.140 line:85% position:50% size:80%
as you realize it's drifted far away.

00:21:53.617 --> 00:21:56.442 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I've been through a lot
in those last forty years.

00:21:56.528 --> 00:22:00.007 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
And now, the light is much
more distant than it's ever been.

00:22:00.093 --> 00:22:05.657 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I shouldn't encourage you
to take this road but trust me,

00:22:06.416 --> 00:22:09.854 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
without that bitterness,
without that hope

00:22:12.041 --> 00:22:13.667 line:85% position:50% size:80%
life would be pathetic.

00:22:26.958 --> 00:22:32.644 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Relax. She's short-sighted
and doesn't wear glasses.

00:22:32.750 --> 00:22:34.736 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Wait a second.
- Sure.

00:22:46.750 --> 00:22:48.993 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Chili? Chili!

00:22:56.125 --> 00:22:57.637 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You don't recognize me?

00:22:59.958 --> 00:23:01.061 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Hi.

00:23:02.416 --> 00:23:04.117 line:85% position:50% size:80%
May I kiss your hand?

00:23:08.833 --> 00:23:09.968 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Witek!

00:23:11.125 --> 00:23:12.792 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Can we talk?
- Sure.

00:23:16.666 --> 00:23:17.950 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Will you wait?

00:23:21.416 --> 00:23:22.586 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Who is he?

00:23:23.708 --> 00:23:26.250 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
My first love.
I'll be right back.

00:23:40.291 --> 00:23:43.718 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Goodbye then. Remember to
switch off the gas.

00:23:46.208 --> 00:23:47.401 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Wait...

00:23:49.416 --> 00:23:55.381 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Adam gave me his card.
In case I needed anything...

00:23:56.458 --> 00:23:59.173 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- So?
- I'm not sure what to do.

00:24:00.791 --> 00:24:02.212 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Do as you please.

00:25:26.916 --> 00:25:28.506 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Applying for a passport?

00:25:30.333 --> 00:25:32.138 line:85% position:50% size:80%
No. For Party membership.

00:25:42.791 --> 00:25:46.596 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Pity we didn't sleep together
when we were seventeen.

00:26:11.083 --> 00:26:14.051 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Farmer? There is Stanisławski.

00:26:14.708 --> 00:26:16.403 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Sportsman Jacek Wszoła.

00:26:17.778 --> 00:26:20.069 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Zimerman, of course!

00:26:21.166 --> 00:26:24.406 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Engineer? I'm not sure.
It says "mechanic" here.

00:26:24.833 --> 00:26:29.565 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Buzek. Yes, I'll double-check.
Idziak and Buzek.

00:26:33.541 --> 00:26:34.676 line:85% position:50% size:80%
May I?

00:26:40.708 --> 00:26:44.470 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Excuse me, there's a problem
with the list of young Poles...

00:26:45.161 --> 00:26:47.582 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- They're asking who these are.
- Close the door.

00:26:47.666 --> 00:26:49.076 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Who is he?
- Witek.

00:26:49.458 --> 00:26:52.477 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Please sit down, Witek.
Join us.

00:26:56.583 --> 00:27:01.762 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
We have a problem. There is
a riot in one of our detox centers.

00:27:03.375 --> 00:27:06.058 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- I don't follow.
- Junkies. Grass, acid...

00:27:06.291 --> 00:27:07.508 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Drug addicts.

00:27:08.833 --> 00:27:10.910 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We took them under our wing.

00:27:11.219 --> 00:27:15.099 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Restaffed the centre with
young doctors and nurses.

00:27:15.291 --> 00:27:18.646 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But they say they don't want
the young ones.

00:27:18.916 --> 00:27:21.166 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And threaten to set the place on fire.

00:27:22.875 --> 00:27:26.791 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
The simplest way would be
to call the police but...

00:27:27.583 --> 00:27:29.202 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Someone has to go there.

00:27:31.291 --> 00:27:33.583 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You know what I think?
Do you?

00:27:37.083 --> 00:27:40.838 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
He can go!
What do you say, Witek?

00:27:42.458 --> 00:27:45.221 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
He was the one in
the green jacket!

00:27:47.368 --> 00:27:48.740 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We can't go.

00:27:49.083 --> 00:27:52.587 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
We're very unpopular there
and we could only make things worse.

00:27:52.673 --> 00:27:54.690 line:85% position:50% size:80%
But you... Give it a try.

00:27:54.818 --> 00:27:59.402 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Comrade Adam spoke well of him,
didn't he?

00:27:59.958 --> 00:28:02.457 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Would you do it?
- I can go...

00:28:02.541 --> 00:28:05.074 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But what should I do
when I get there?

00:28:07.083 --> 00:28:08.252 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Calm them down.

00:28:08.337 --> 00:28:10.664 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Do whatever it takes
to calm them down.

00:28:10.750 --> 00:28:14.634 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
We'll be here, by the phone.
Keep the line open.

00:28:14.875 --> 00:28:17.484 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- He'll need a car.
- What about the list?

00:28:20.508 --> 00:28:21.583 line:85% position:50% size:80%
What list?

00:28:21.669 --> 00:28:25.058 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Who are Buzek and Idziak?
- Look them up, will you?

00:28:26.208 --> 00:28:30.051 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Idziak is a film director,
Buzek, an aircraft engineer.

00:28:30.625 --> 00:28:34.996 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Well then, put on your jacket.
You'll be there in an hour.

00:28:36.791 --> 00:28:37.939 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He'll do it!

00:28:44.958 --> 00:28:48.060 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Our men are on stand-by.
- OK. I'm going.

00:28:52.625 --> 00:28:55.397 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Who is it?
- From the Warsaw Council.

00:28:56.291 --> 00:28:57.429 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Your ID.

00:29:13.166 --> 00:29:14.449 line:85% position:50% size:80%
From Warsaw.

00:29:36.333 --> 00:29:38.031 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We've met before.

00:29:39.791 --> 00:29:42.138 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Długosz. The Warsaw Council.
- Hi.

00:29:44.083 --> 00:29:47.681 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- We have ten of those.
- It'll all burn down in ten minutes.

00:29:47.958 --> 00:29:50.057 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Warsaw area code?
- 8.

00:29:57.416 --> 00:29:59.528 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Like in America, isn't it?

00:30:04.375 --> 00:30:06.008 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Długosz speaking.
I'm here.

00:30:07.500 --> 00:30:11.307 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
The doctors are here.
Locked up.

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:14.519 line:85% position:50% size:80%
No, I just got here.

00:30:15.291 --> 00:30:17.672 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Looks like the director's office.

00:30:18.375 --> 00:30:19.474 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Bye.

00:30:20.291 --> 00:30:22.157 line:85% position:50% size:80%
It's the counselor's office.

00:30:23.625 --> 00:30:28.286 line:85% position:50% size:80%
The director's office is much nicer.

00:30:29.541 --> 00:30:30.711 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Isn't it?

00:30:33.118 --> 00:30:35.194 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He has a palm plant there!

00:30:36.916 --> 00:30:38.166 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Look, pal,

00:30:38.708 --> 00:30:42.539 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
since you guys took over, a girl
and two boys have pulled the plug.

00:30:42.625 --> 00:30:43.623 line:85% position:50% size:80%
They what?

00:30:43.708 --> 00:30:47.866 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Offed themselves. She with poison,
the other two hanged themselves.

00:30:49.208 --> 00:30:51.490 line:85% position:50% size:80%
One spent four days in this cage.

00:30:52.390 --> 00:30:53.578 line:85% position:50% size:80%
And before?

00:30:54.083 --> 00:30:55.207 line:85% position:50% size:80%
No one, ever.

00:30:55.291 --> 00:30:58.143 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- What are your demands?
- Can't you read?

00:31:00.028 --> 00:31:02.544 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Cancel the party's patronage,
bring back the old staff

00:31:02.628 --> 00:31:04.383 line:85% position:50% size:80%
and restore the hospital status.

00:31:04.468 --> 00:31:07.121 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- You're in charge?
- Yes. He's a doctor.

00:31:08.144 --> 00:31:09.332 line:85% position:50% size:80%
She's our therapist.

00:31:09.416 --> 00:31:12.248 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Where's the rest?
- Got away when it started.

00:31:12.333 --> 00:31:14.343 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Can I talk to them?
- Let him.

00:31:18.875 --> 00:31:22.833 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- I'm not sure what to do.
- Try to get us out of here.

00:31:22.917 --> 00:31:26.159 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Who was in charge before?
- Helpless suckers who wanted

00:31:26.243 --> 00:31:30.164 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
to treat addiction with persuasion
while drugs were being smuggled in.

00:31:30.250 --> 00:31:33.108 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- But there were no suicides.
- We saved one.

00:31:33.193 --> 00:31:36.457 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
And we were cleared
of any negligence with the other two.

00:31:36.541 --> 00:31:38.789 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Time's up!
- You think they would burn the place?

00:31:38.875 --> 00:31:41.855 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Sure. They're nuts.
These three and the rest!

00:31:42.625 --> 00:31:44.159 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We're not afraid.

00:31:52.708 --> 00:31:54.250 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Like in America?

00:31:56.833 --> 00:31:59.108 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Can you call a meeting?
- I can.

00:32:01.000 --> 00:32:03.769 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Roll calls in the morning,
then press reviews.

00:32:04.001 --> 00:32:07.582 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
They locked us up, read our letters
and searched our parcels.

00:32:07.666 --> 00:32:09.873 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Finally, they banned all visitors.

00:32:09.958 --> 00:32:11.435 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Gestapo!

00:32:12.791 --> 00:32:15.470 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
And they've made me
a group leader.

00:32:15.666 --> 00:32:18.250 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Do I look like a group leader?

00:32:19.333 --> 00:32:23.708 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I barely knew the old director,
but I thought he liked us.

00:32:24.208 --> 00:32:25.781 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He liked Staszek, too.

00:32:26.291 --> 00:32:28.319 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
They caged him
for making love to me.

00:32:28.404 --> 00:32:30.886 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Staszek was the one
who hanged himself.

00:32:34.666 --> 00:32:38.396 line:85% position:50% size:80%
<i>We're roaming the world</i>

00:32:39.083 --> 00:32:41.832 line:85% position:50% size:80%
<i>in search of a brand new life.</i>

00:32:41.916 --> 00:32:48.724 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
<i>We keep looking forward
</i><i>to yet another love.</i>

00:32:50.166 --> 00:32:53.873 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
<i>- We are different...</i><i>
</i><i>- A call for you.</i>

00:32:53.958 --> 00:32:57.323 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
<i>that's why you
</i><i>don't want to know us.</i>

00:32:57.791 --> 00:33:03.078 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
<i>We are different
</i><i>but capable of so much...</i>

00:33:06.916 --> 00:33:08.053 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Hello?

00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:09.876 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Yeah, a meeting.

00:33:11.666 --> 00:33:12.964 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Hold on.

00:33:33.083 --> 00:33:34.402 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Jump!

00:33:40.750 --> 00:33:41.849 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Hurry.

00:33:55.083 --> 00:33:57.481 line:85% position:50% size:80%
They got away! They ran!

00:33:57.958 --> 00:33:59.385 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Bring the fuel cans!

00:34:01.750 --> 00:34:03.244 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Gasoline!

00:34:05.217 --> 00:34:07.236 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Everyone to the corridor!
Spill it! Quickly!

00:34:07.320 --> 00:34:08.882 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Run! I'm staying.

00:34:09.791 --> 00:34:12.248 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Stop! Don't do it!
You got me!

00:34:12.333 --> 00:34:13.496 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Get him!

00:34:17.333 --> 00:34:19.539 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Bring the buckets and bowls!

00:34:19.625 --> 00:34:21.646 line:85% position:50% size:80%
It's too slow from the cans.

00:34:22.916 --> 00:34:24.650 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Use the bowls.

00:34:24.800 --> 00:34:26.043 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Lock it!

00:34:32.416 --> 00:34:34.065 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Did you hear?

00:34:34.791 --> 00:34:35.903 line:85% position:50% size:80%
What?

00:34:36.458 --> 00:34:39.380 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I stayed so they didn't
burn the place down!

00:34:39.541 --> 00:34:41.128 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Yes, three demands.

00:34:42.458 --> 00:34:44.427 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I think they're right!

00:34:45.791 --> 00:34:48.639 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
We're waiting till eight,
then we'll burn it all.

00:35:07.750 --> 00:35:10.331 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
It's just water. To test
how it spills.

00:35:10.416 --> 00:35:11.518 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Relax.

00:35:25.416 --> 00:35:29.445 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You got off to a good start.
That moment of weakness helped.

00:35:29.625 --> 00:35:31.364 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- I was scared.
- I know.

00:35:32.500 --> 00:35:36.574 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But you should know that
such moments can be useful.

00:35:37.666 --> 00:35:40.871 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Such a moment of weakness
makes you just like them.

00:35:41.416 --> 00:35:46.469 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
They drop their guard
and you gain the upper hand.

00:35:46.875 --> 00:35:49.043 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You shouldn't have said
they were right.

00:35:49.128 --> 00:35:50.358 line:85% position:50% size:80%
They were.

00:35:51.117 --> 00:35:53.164 line:85% position:50% size:80%
But why say that in front of them?

00:35:53.250 --> 00:35:56.914 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
If better timed, the truth can serve
a purpose - add to your prestige,

00:35:57.000 --> 00:35:59.873 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- help obtain concessions...
- I wanted to play fair.

00:35:59.958 --> 00:36:02.532 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
You were there in
an official capacity.

00:36:02.655 --> 00:36:06.045 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
If you were there as a private person,
you'd have acted differently.

00:36:06.130 --> 00:36:07.257 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Why?

00:36:07.666 --> 00:36:08.916 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I was alone.

00:36:09.375 --> 00:36:14.625 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
No. You had a phone, the police
and the authorities to fall back on.

00:36:14.958 --> 00:36:17.422 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Otherwise, you'd have
been scared.

00:36:19.875 --> 00:36:23.088 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- Krystyna, this is Mr. Długosz.
- Hello.

00:36:27.541 --> 00:36:30.978 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Was it you who called us
last year, before Werner left?

00:36:31.132 --> 00:36:32.311 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Yes.

00:36:33.791 --> 00:36:36.315 line:85% position:50% size:80%
We used to be friends long ago...

00:36:36.500 --> 00:36:38.806 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
He told me.
He told me many things.

00:36:39.000 --> 00:36:40.733 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- About prison?
- That too.

00:36:42.166 --> 00:36:46.213 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Had he been released first,
our lives would have gone differently.

00:36:46.297 --> 00:36:48.206 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He'd be here now.

00:36:48.291 --> 00:36:50.539 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You think it was blind chance?

00:36:50.625 --> 00:36:55.539 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
He was beaten into a false confession.
It's a matter of character.

00:36:55.625 --> 00:36:57.114 line:85% position:50% size:80%
I was beaten.

00:36:58.583 --> 00:37:07.153 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
But for the next fifteen years
I've exercised my legs.

00:37:08.125 --> 00:37:10.250 line:85% position:50% size:80%
He didn't have a purpose.

00:37:10.541 --> 00:37:15.110 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
How can one believe in something
that almost destroyed him?

00:37:16.416 --> 00:37:18.983 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Every idea has its period of errors.

00:37:19.541 --> 00:37:21.846 line:85% position:50% size:80%
The Inquisition did worse things,

00:37:22.416 --> 00:37:25.311 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
yet people died at the stake
having faith in God.

00:37:25.625 --> 00:37:28.748 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Then, John XXIII breathed new life
into the Church.

00:37:28.833 --> 00:37:32.039 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Are you sure this period
of errors won't happen again?

00:37:32.125 --> 00:37:33.456 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- In this country?
- Yes.

00:37:33.541 --> 00:37:41.574 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Am I sure? Right now,
in this country,

00:37:43.083 --> 00:37:45.326 line:85% position:50% size:80%
everything's falling apart.

00:37:46.666 --> 00:37:52.094 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Those who govern are helpless.

00:37:52.708 --> 00:37:54.862 line:85% position:50% size:80%
This system is doomed.

00:37:56.083 --> 00:37:57.706 line:85% position:50% size:80%
It's just a matter of time.

00:37:57.791 --> 00:37:59.590 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Is that what you think?

00:38:00.375 --> 00:38:03.534 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- And you say it?
- Out loud? Yes.

00:38:03.750 --> 00:38:04.989 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Why to me?

00:38:05.250 --> 00:38:08.623 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Because those at
the top won't listen.

00:38:08.708 --> 00:38:11.956 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
I need someone to back me up.
Maybe people like you?

00:38:12.041 --> 00:38:14.947 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- So what should be done?
- Adam!

00:38:16.893 --> 00:38:18.039 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Excuse me.

00:38:27.875 --> 00:38:29.003 line:85% position:50% size:80%
The scissors...

00:38:34.518 --> 00:38:37.280 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
- What was I saying?
- I asked what should be done.

00:38:37.364 --> 00:38:39.483 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You have to be on the inside.

00:38:40.666 --> 00:38:43.210 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Nothing can be improved
from the outside.

00:38:43.570 --> 00:38:45.490 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
When all of this
comes tumbling down

00:38:45.576 --> 00:38:47.498 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
someone has to be there
to pick up the pieces.

00:38:47.583 --> 00:38:48.686 line:85% position:50% size:80%
Who?

00:38:49.666 --> 00:38:51.878 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You, me... Someone.

00:38:53.625 --> 00:38:58.396 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
We can't leave this
country to them, can we?

00:38:59.791 --> 00:39:01.809 line:85% position:50% size:80%
You know what terrifies me?

00:39:02.208 --> 00:39:08.277 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:80%
Losing freedom. Being under
somebody's thumb.

